featured_reviews.review_id:
The Bahadur Tari Mosque is ideally situated on the North Bank of the Brahmaputra river, on the Sounthern end of Dhubri town. It is connected with the main town by a single lane  road. It is accessible by car, two wheeler and bicycles.
The area is very congested, the roads are narrow and doesnot have any parking place.
The mosque is neither very big nor small but it is built nicely. It is surrounded by a small market place containing shops of different kinds. It doesnot have any hotels. There are small dhabas scattered around the mosque.
Bahadurtari is a ferryghat providing a facility of mechanised boats for crossing the Brahmaputra river.
It doesnot have anything to boast of other than the mosque.
It doesnot have anything worth to attract a general tourist.
A photo of the place will be added to the comment when I visit the place next time.

featured_reviews.review_id: The area called Islamnagar is a suburban southern part of Dhubri town adjoining the North Bank of the Brahmaputra river. It still lacks basic civic facilities but inhabited mostly by local immigrants( not outsiders) who were disturbed by the mass soil erosion due to the overflowing and unchecked river because their parental houses and properties got washed away. The population is mosltly muslims who have constructed nothing else but a number of mosques around them to remain contended with their destiny. One of the mosques is centrally located in the area and is called Islamnagar mosque which is situated by the side of a muddy road ( not concrete) unsuitable even for a walk during rainy seasons. Does not provide for parking of cars or any other vehicle.

featured_reviews.review_id:
This a beautifully constructed mosque on IG Road that is a motorable road  connecting Amco Road to Dhubri Railway station @ Amco road kabaristan.
IG Road is a 20'wide road with human dwellings along both side of the road, right from the beginning to the end. Of course, the road has been encroached upon at places along its length to render it narrower at places down the stretch.
The mosque is well conceived, well planned, well constructed double storey building to accomodate almost 500-600 people simultaneously for the Prayers. From
Hyegine point of view, it is bit poor and shows lack of clenliness around the mosque.
There is no tea stall, hotel or any shop around the mosque.
